Wash and dry produce.

Trim and roughly chop @scallions{2}. Peel and mince @garlic{1%clove}. Zest and quarter @lime{1}. Dice @tomato{1}. Drain and rinse @black beans{1%can}.

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{3/4%cup} (1 1/2 cups for 4 servings), and a big pinch of @salt{}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce heat to low. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, in a #small bowl{}, combine scallions, @olive oil{2%tbsp}, and @southwest spice blend{1%tsp} (you'll use more in the next step). Stir in a pinch of garlic and a squeeze of lime juice to taste. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Taste and add more garlic and lime juice as needed.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%tsp} in a #medium pot{} over medium-high heat. Add tomato and remaining garlic; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add beans, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, @water{1/2%cup} (1/3 cup for 4 servings), @southwest spice blend{1%tsp} (1 TBSP for 4), salt, and pepper. (You'll use the rest of the Southwest Spice Blend in the next step.) Simmer until thickened, ~{5-10%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4). Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}. Season with remaining @southwest spice blend{1%tsp}, salt, and pepper.

> Swap in chicken or beef for pork. Cook chicken until browned and cooked through, 3-5 minutes per side, or cook beef to desired doneness, 4-7 minutes per side.

Heat a drizzle of cooking oil in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes} per side.

Transfer to a #cutting board{}.

While chicken cooks, in a second small bowl, combine @sour cream{1.5%tbsp}, half the lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, and a big pinch of salt. Stir in water 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings), remaining lime zest, a squeeze of lime juice, salt, and pepper.

Once cool enough to handle, slice chicken crosswise.

Divide rice and chicken between plates. Top rice with bean mixture and crema. Top chicken with salsa. Cut any remaining lime into smaller wedges and serve on the side.

> Once cool enough to handle, thinly slice chicken or beef against the grain.